HEADWORD: Sea fowl
<hw>Sea" fowl`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any bird which
habitually frequents the sea, as an auk, gannet, gull, tern, or petrel;
also, all such birds, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

